---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { useTranslations } from '../../../i18n/ui';

const lang = 'en';
const t = useTranslations(lang);
---

<BaseLayout title={t('docs.features.title')} lang={lang}>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">
        <a href="/en/" class="hover:text-gray-300">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <a href="/en/docs/features" class="text-gray-300">Features</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">{t('docs.features.title')}</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-400">{t('docs.features.subtitle')}</p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-12">
      <a href="#memory" class="text-sm bg-gray-800/50 hover:bg-gray-800 text-gray-300 hover:text-white px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg transition-colors">Memory</a>
      <a href="#subagents" class="text-sm bg-gray-800/50 hover:bg-gray-800 text-gray-300 hover:text-white px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg transition-colors">Subagents</a>
      <a href="#platforms" class="text-sm bg-gray-800/50 hover:bg-gray-800 text-gray-300 hover:text-white px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg transition-colors">Platforms</a>
      <a href="#scheduling" class="text-sm bg-gray-800/50 hover:bg-gray-800 text-gray-300 hover:text-white px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg transition-colors">Scheduling</a>
      <a href="#skills" class="text-sm bg-gray-800/50 hover:bg-gray-800 text-gray-300 hover:text-white px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg transition-colors">Skills</a>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-content">
      <h2 id="memory">{t('docs.features.memory')}</h2>
      <p>Hermes Agent features industry-leading persistent memory. Unlike traditional "stateless" chatbots, Hermes remembers everything it learns, and the longer you use it, the better it understands you.</p>

      <h3>Key Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Agent-curated memory</strong> — the agent autonomously decides what's worth remembering and periodically nudges itself to persist important knowledge</li>
        <li><strong>Auto skill generation</strong> — after complex tasks, the agent distills solutions into reusable skills</li>
        <li><strong>Cross-session search</strong> — FTS5 full-text search across all conversation history with LLM summarization</li>
        <li><strong>User modeling</strong> — Honcho dialectic user modeling builds an ever-deepening model of who you are</li>
        <li><strong>agentskills.io standard</strong> — compatible with the open skills standard for cross-agent sharing</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>How It Works</h3>
      <p>When you converse with Hermes Agent, it stores information at three levels:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Working memory</strong> — context within the current conversation</li>
        <li><strong>Persistent memory</strong> — important facts, preferences, and knowledge retained across conversations</li>
        <li><strong>Skill library</strong> — standardized procedures distilled from experience</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 id="subagents">{t('docs.features.subagents')}</h2>
      <p>Hermes Agent can spawn isolated subagents to work on tasks in parallel. Each subagent has its own conversation context, terminal environment, and toolset.</p>

      <h3>Key Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Isolated execution</strong> — each subagent has independent conversation history and terminal</li>
        <li><strong>Parallel processing</strong> — handle multiple tasks simultaneously</li>
        <li><strong>Python RPC</strong> — write Python scripts that call tools via RPC, collapsing multi-step pipelines into zero-context-cost turns</li>
        <li><strong>Flexible orchestration</strong> — the main agent coordinates subagent workflows and aggregates results</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Use Cases</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Simultaneous code reviews across multiple repositories</li>
        <li>Parallel research on multiple topics with consolidated reports</li>
        <li>Batch data processing tasks</li>
        <li>Complex multi-step workflows decomposed into parallel subtasks</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="platforms">{t('docs.features.platforms')}</h2>
      <p>Hermes Agent connects to multiple messaging platforms through a single gateway process. Start a conversation on Telegram and continue on Discord — the context carries over seamlessly.</p>

      <h3>Supported Platforms</h3>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Platform</th><th>Features</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Telegram</td><td>Full support including voice memo transcription and file transfer</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Discord</td><td>Full support with channels and DMs</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Slack</td><td>Full support, ideal for team collaboration</td></tr>
          <tr><td>WhatsApp</td><td>Send and receive messages</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Signal</td><td>Send and receive messages</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Email</td><td>Send and receive emails</td></tr>
          <tr><td>CLI</td><td>Full TUI with multiline editing, history, and streaming output</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>Quick Setup</h3>
      <div class="code-block my-4">
        <pre><code>hermes gateway setup    # Configure messaging platforms
hermes gateway start    # Start the gateway</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h2 id="scheduling">{t('docs.features.scheduling')}</h2>
      <p>Hermes Agent includes a built-in cron scheduler with natural language support. Set up daily news digests, weekly reports, or periodic backups — all running unattended.</p>

      <h3>Key Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Natural language scheduling</strong> — describe tasks in plain language, no cron syntax needed</li>
        <li><strong>Multi-platform delivery</strong> — deliver scheduled task results to any connected platform</li>
        <li><strong>Persistence</strong> — scheduled tasks survive agent restarts</li>
        <li><strong>Flexible configuration</strong> — one-time and recurring tasks</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Examples</h3>
      <div class="code-block my-4">
        <pre><code># Set up scheduled tasks in natural language
"Send me a daily news digest at 9 AM"
"Back up the /data directory every Monday"
"Check server status every hour and send a report"</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h2 id="skills">{t('docs.features.skills')}</h2>
      <p>Hermes Agent features a complete skills learning loop — its core differentiator. It doesn't just use predefined skills; it creates new ones from experience and continuously improves them.</p>

      <h3>Skill Ecosystem</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>77 built-in skills</strong> — coding, search, document processing, multimedia, and more</li>
        <li><strong>45 optional skills</strong> — advanced features requiring additional dependencies</li>
        <li><strong>521 community skills</strong> — community contributions, continuously growing</li>
        <li><strong>16 categories</strong> — AI coding, system administration, research, multimedia creation, etc.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Learning Loop</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Task execution</strong> — the agent completes a complex task</li>
        <li><strong>Skill extraction</strong> — automatically analyzes the solution and distills it into a reusable skill</li>
        <li><strong>Skill storage</strong> — saves to the local skill library</li>
        <li><strong>Self-improvement</strong> — optimizes the skill based on feedback during subsequent use</li>
        <li><strong>Knowledge persistence</strong> — self-nudge mechanism ensures experience is never forgotten</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Browsing Skills</h3>
      <div class="code-block my-4">
        <pre><code>/skills              # Browse all available skills
/&lt;skill-name&gt;        # Directly invoke a skill</code></pre>
      </div>
      <p>Visit the <a href="https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/docs/skills" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Skills Hub</a> to browse the complete skill catalog.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
